OL,5,Cpaused
OL,7,FIn a speech to the House of Commons,
OL,8,Fthe Chancellor said "if we cannot
OL,9,Fafford it, we cannot do it," as she
OL,10,Fset out a series of "difficult
OL,11,Fchoices" needed to make big savings.
OL,13,FAccording to Labour, there is a #22
OL,14,Fbillion hole in the public finances,
OL,15,Fwhich the Party has firmly blamed on
OL,16,Fthe former Conservative government,
OL,17,Fclaiming it overspent this year's
OL,18,Fbudgets by billions of pounds after
OL,19,Fmaking a series of "unfunded
OL,20,Fcommitments".
